                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>The editor alerts the reader to the advertisement of Fr. Scheffer,
                    proprietor of the Virginia Hotel. Scheffer offers rooms by the day or longer,
                    his stables are open and stocked, and his dining room, under the direction of
                    Messrs. Smith and Beard, offers meals of anything available in the markets of
                    Staunton or Richmond.</summary>
                <note/>
